    <h1>Ai Wei Wei, @aiww</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200721/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-07-21"><time>2020-07-21</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | ARTS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>So what did the Chi­nese artist get up to? He launched the Ai Wei Wei mask cam­paign, where hand-printed masks (one with an im­age of a mid­dle fin­ger held up) were sold on eBay to raise money for or­gan­i­sa­tions such as Hu­man Rights Watch, Refugees In­ter­na­tional, and Doc­tors With­out Bor­ders.</p>
    <p>As of last week, the cam­paign had raised</p>
    <p>US$1.4 mil­lion (S$1.95 mil­lion) and many have posted im­ages of them­selves in the masks on­line.</p>

